(59, 20, '10 Best Operating Systems for Laptops and Computers [2020 LIST]', '<p><strong>List of The Top and Most Popular Operating Systems with Features and Comparison. Pick The Best OS for Your Business or Personal Use From This List:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Today&rsquo;s modern age is blessed with the miracle of technology. One of these miracles that have made our lives simpler, faster and more entertaining is the computers.</p>\r\n<p>Computers are a revolutionary invention that really changed the course of human civilization. It has evolved from bulky desktop boxes to more portable and convenient laptops and mobile phones.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>However, the fact which many seldom talk about is what makes these computers work the way they do. We are of course talking about the operating system aka OS. Without an operating system, a computer cannot simply function.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src="https://cdn.softwaretestinghelp.com/wp-content/qa/uploads/2019/09/OPerating-Systems-list.png" alt="https://cdn.softwaretestinghelp.com/wp-content/qa/uploads/2019/09/OPerating-Systems-list.png" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span id="What_Is_The_Difference_Between_Server_OS_And_Everyday_OS">What Is The Difference Between Server OS And Everyday OS?</span></h2>\r\n<p>Understanding how to differentiate a server OS from an everyday one is vital to our discussion. The differences are very specific.</p>\r\n<p>An everyday OS will be able to run programs like MS Word, PowerPoint, Excel, etc. including running one of your favorite video games. It enables applications that make browsing the web and checking emails easy. It uses LAN and Bluetooth connections and is cheaper than a server OS.</p>\r\n<p>Server OS, on the other hand, are expensive and rightfully so. These platforms enable unlimited user connections, a greater memory capacity, and act as universal servers for web, emails, and databases.</p>\r\n<p>A server OS can handle multiple desktops as it is optimized for a network instead of catering to a single user.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span id="What_Is_An_Operating_System">What Is An Operating System?</span></h2>\r\n<p>An operating system in its most general definition is the software that allows a user to run crucial applications on his/her computing device. It helps to manage a computer&rsquo;s hardware resources. It helps to support basic functions like scheduling tasks, and controlling peripherals.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Which OS Is Best For Personal Use?</strong></p>\r\n<p>When it comes to home use, traditional Windows and MAC OS are great options. At home, you don&rsquo;t need powerful OS especially for simple tasks like writing or browsing the web. For gaming, the Windows operating system is well optimized than that of MAC.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Which Is The Fastest OS?</strong></p>\r\n<p>While discussing the fastest OS, there is no argument that Linux based OS is the lightest and fastest OS in the market right now. It doesn&rsquo;t need a powerful processor unlike Windows to operate at an optimal level.</p>\r\n<p>Linux based OS like Ubuntu Server, CentOS server, Fedora is great options especially for running business enterprises where substantial computing power is mandatory.</p>\r\n<h3><span id="Free_Operating_System_Alternatives">Free Operating System Alternatives</span></h3>\r\n<p>We understand that not everyone has enough dollars to afford a high-grade operating system for their computers. However, that&rsquo;s not all the bad news as there are free OS alternatives which ensure that your computer keeps running. All the below options are available for download, hence you can simply install it today.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Linux: </strong>Linux is absolutely free and will literally run on anything.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Chrome OS: </strong>Chrome OS is available on a number of Low cost and some high-end laptops, like chrome books.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Free BSD: </strong>With its roots connected to Linux, it is the modern-day version of the Berkeley Software Distribution.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Syllable: </strong>Syllable is yet another free alternative for home and small business users only.</li>\r\n<li><strong>ReactOS: </strong>Initially launched as a Windows 95 clone, this OS has come a long way since then.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Notable mentions go to OS like <em>Haiku, MorphOS, Android.</em></strong></p>\r\n<p><img src="https://cdn.softwaretestinghelp.com/wp-content/qa/uploads/2019/09/OS_Market_Share.png" alt="https://cdn.softwaretestinghelp.com/wp-content/qa/uploads/2019/09/OS_Market_Share.png" /></p>', 'reda', 'programming', 'post5f95ae55c4909.png', '2020-10-25'),
(60, 20, 'Top 10 Best Linux Distros 2020', '<h2><span id="the-best-linux-distros-2020">The Best Linux Distros 2020</span></h2>\r\n<p>Let&rsquo;s get down to the list of the best Linux distros and what makes them better than the others. Now as we previously mentioned, all of the configurations that were achieved by any of the distributions in the list below can be achieved on any other distribution. So we&rsquo;re working with their out-of-the-box experiences.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div data-zone="jd_post_mid_300x250" data-format="300x250" data-publisher="www.journaldev.com" data-type="ad">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2><span id="1-mx-linux">#1 MX Linux</span></h2>\r\n<div>\r\n<figure><img src="https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/MX-linux-screenshot.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" srcset="https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/MX-linux-screenshot.jpg 1280w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/MX-linux-screenshot-450x281.jpg 450w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/MX-linux-screenshot-1024x640.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/MX-linux-screenshot-768x480.jpg 768w" alt="MX Linux best linux distros 2020" width="600" height="" loading="lazy" />\r\n<figcaption>MX Linux Screenshot</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>We loved MX Linux because it&rsquo;s fully set up out of the box. But unlike Ubuntu, <strong>MX Linux is set up with all that a beginner user would need while keeping the UI very simple, clean, and lightweight.</strong></p>\r\n<p>MX Linux is based on Debian&rsquo;s Stable branch and uses XFCE as it&rsquo;s default desktop environment (UI).</p>\r\n<p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://mxlinux.org/">https://mxlinux.org/</a></p>\r\n<h2><span id="2-linux-mint">#2 Linux Mint</span></h2>\r\n<div>\r\n<figure><img src="https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Linux-mint-screenshots.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 1200px" srcset="https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Linux-mint-screenshots.jpg 1200w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Linux-mint-screenshots-450x281.jpg 450w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Linux-mint-screenshots-1024x640.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Linux-mint-screenshots-768x480.jpg 768w" alt="Linux Mint top 10 best linux distributions in 2020" width="600" height="375" loading="lazy" />\r\n<figcaption>Linux Mint Screenshots</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Linux Mint is a behemoth! The Goliath in the world of Linux distributions. Similar to Ubuntu, Linux Mint took off very quickly when it was first launched.</p>\r\n<p>Linux Mint focused not just on ease of use but also focused on adding many convenient tools for their users. Along with that, they offered a lightweight desktop environment.</p>\r\n<p><strong>So, people who wanted their Linux to be fast on lower-end systems, Linux Mint became the choice of distro.</strong></p>\r\n<p>This distro is based on Ubuntu-Debian, so it is compatible with the repositories of both the distros.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://linuxmint.com/" aria-invalid="true">https://linuxmint.com/</a></p>\r\n<h2><span id="3-ubuntu">#3 Ubuntu</span></h2>\r\n<div>\r\n<figure><img src="https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/ubuntu-linux-screenshot-1024x576.png" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/ubuntu-linux-screenshot-1024x576.png 1024w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/ubuntu-linux-screenshot-450x253.png 450w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/ubuntu-linux-screenshot-768x432.png 768w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/ubuntu-linux-screenshot-1536x864.png 1536w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/ubuntu-linux-screenshot.png 1920w" alt="Ubuntu Linux Screenshot" width="512" height="250" loading="lazy" />\r\n<figcaption>Ubuntu Linux Screenshot</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll hear about Ubuntu even before you&rsquo;ve thought of trying Linux. And obviously so because Ubuntu was the first distribution that worked really hard to make itself stand out in the Linux distribution crowd when it all started.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Ubuntu made Linux accessible to the entire world by making it so easy to use, that a person who had never seen Linux would be able to use it pretty much right away.</strong></p>\r\n<p>As they progressed, they added more and more features to their OS, also tried to launch a Ubuntu TV, but it all ended up making Ubuntu desktop really heavy on the resources and slowing things. Other distributions capitalized on this opportunity and picked up where Ubuntu left things off.</p>\r\n<p>Ubuntu is a Debian-based distribution.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Website</strong>: <a href="https://ubuntu.com/">https://ubuntu.com/</a></p>\r\n<h2><span id="4-elementary-os">#4 Elementary OS</span></h2>\r\n<div>\r\n<figure><img src="https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/elementary-os-screenshot-1-1024x576.png" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/elementary-os-screenshot-1-1024x576.png 1024w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/elementary-os-screenshot-1-450x253.png 450w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/elementary-os-screenshot-1-768x432.png 768w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/elementary-os-screenshot-1-1536x864.png 1536w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/elementary-os-screenshot-1.png 1920w" alt="Elementary Os Screenshot 1" width="512" height="300" loading="lazy" />\r\n<figcaption>Elementary Os Screenshot 1</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>This is by far the most beautiful Linux distribution that we came across. Inspired by the Mac OS, it has a dock at the bottom and the menus at the top of the screen.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The entire UI is very slick. If all you want is a beautiful OS, Elementary OS is the way to go.</strong></p>\r\n<p>Obviously, since it&rsquo;s Debian based, you&rsquo;re not going to lack functionality or packages. The only issue you&rsquo;d face from time to time is that there are packages that just don&rsquo;t adjust to the distribution&rsquo;s theme. So you will always have some packages that look odd when opened.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://elementary.io/">https://elementary.io/</a></p>\r\n<h2><span id="5-manjaro-linux">#5 Manjaro Linux</span></h2>\r\n<div>\r\n<figure><img src="https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/manjaro-linux-screenshot.jpeg" sizes="(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px" srcset="https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/manjaro-linux-screenshot.jpeg 1920w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/manjaro-linux-screenshot-450x253.jpeg 450w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/manjaro-linux-screenshot-1024x576.jpeg 1024w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/manjaro-linux-screenshot-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/manjaro-linux-screenshot-1536x864.jpeg 1536w" alt="Manjaro Linux Screenshot" width="500" height="270" loading="lazy" />\r\n<figcaption>Manjaro Linux Screenshot</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Manjaro Linux is an Arch Linux-based distribution. Arch was also built to be more up-to-date than Debian with a repository that makes cutting edge software to be available.</p>\r\n<p>Compared to Debian, the one major difference between Arch-based operating systems is their leanness. Debian, in an effort to make things easy for the user, installs a bunch of &ldquo;recommended&rdquo; packages when you try to install any package from their repositories.</p>\r\n<p>With Arch Linux, when you&rsquo;re installing a package, you get exactly that and a few of the dependencies which are resolved by its package manager, <strong>Pacman</strong>.</p>\r\n<div data-block="3" data-code="" data-insertion-no-dbg="" data-selector=".ai-insert-3-10609999" data-insertion="after">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div data-zone="jd_middle_post_desktop" data-format="728x90" data-publisher="www.journaldev.com" data-type="ad"><iframe id="dm-gpt-iframe-3" width="380" height="45" frameborder="0" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" scrolling="no" data-mce-fragment="1"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>So if you&rsquo;re into lean systems, and want to build yourself a computer with a really lean and fast operating system, Arch Linux-based Manjaro is the way to go. </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://manjaro.org/">https://manjaro.org/</a></p>\r\n<h2><span id="6-zorin-os">#6 Zorin OS</span></h2>\r\n<div>\r\n<figure><img src="https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/zorin-os-screenshot-1.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 1368px) 100vw, 1368px" srcset="https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/zorin-os-screenshot-1.jpg 1368w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/zorin-os-screenshot-1-450x253.jpg 450w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/zorin-os-screenshot-1-1024x575.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/zorin-os-screenshot-1-768x431.jpg 768w" alt="Zorin Os Screenshot" width="650" height="350" loading="lazy" />\r\n<figcaption>Zorin Os Screenshot</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re coming from Windows, and have never used Linux before, Zorin takes away a huge load of the learning curve for you. See the screenshot above. What do you notice?</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s exactly like Windows. Well, a much more beautiful version of Windows. Based on Ubuntu, it is as accessible as Linux can be. <strong>So if you&rsquo;re looking for a Linux distro that can help you minimize the learning curve of coming from Windows, this is what you should start with.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://zorinos.com/">https://zorinos.com/</a></p>\r\n<h2><span id="7-fedora">#7 Fedora</span></h2>\r\n<figure><img src="https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/fedora-linux-screenshots-1024x640.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/fedora-linux-screenshots-1024x640.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/fedora-linux-screenshots-450x281.jpg 450w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/fedora-linux-screenshots-768x480.jpg 768w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/fedora-linux-screenshots.jpg 1280w" alt="Fedora Linux Screenshots" width="512" height="320" loading="lazy" />\r\n<figcaption>Fedora Linux Screenshots</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>Fedora is not based on any other Linux distribution and has been built by its community entirely from scratch. In fact, if you&rsquo;re a developer, you can contribute to the distribution too.</p>\r\n<p>What makes Fedora so special is its community support. The community is very responsive and you can get answers to your question pretty quickly on there.</p>\r\n<p>Since it&rsquo;s built by developers, their focus was on creating an OS that will have a really cutting edge software repository. A package which is still unavailable in other distributions will be compiled and ready for Fedora irrespective of the fact if it&rsquo;s stable or not.</p>\r\n<p><strong>If you love the latest and the greatest and are okay with a few bugs in downloaded packages from time to time, Fedora is your abode. </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://getfedora.org/">https://getfedora.org/</a></p>\r\n<h2><span id="8-debian">#8 Debian</span></h2>\r\n<figure><img src="https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/debian-screenshot-1024x640.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/debian-screenshot-1024x640.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/debian-screenshot-450x281.jpg 450w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/debian-screenshot-768x480.jpg 768w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/debian-screenshot.jpg 1280w" alt="Debian Screenshot" width="512" height="320" loading="lazy" />\r\n<figcaption>Debian Screenshot</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>Debian, CentOS, and Red Hat powers the internet around the world. As per statistics, more than 96% of the web servers, cloud hosts, and websites, are powered by Linux.</p>\r\n<p>But Debian wasn&rsquo;t built to be userfriendly or to offer a quick and easy out of the box experience. When you download and run live Debian, all you get is a black terminal screen with a prompt at the top left of your screen.</p>\r\n<p>Unlike the pre-built distributions that we saw before, Debian allows you a more do-it-yourself experience. You choose the packages that you want to install, the desktop environment that you want, and any additions that you want to the OS.</p>\r\n<p>You can think of Debian as stock Android. MIUI, eUI, and Samsung UI are built on stock Android. These UIs created by companies for their phones can be compared with the Linux distributions which are built on Debian.</p>\r\n<p><strong>If you want an extremely stable operating system that you wish to build from scratch, Debian is your answer.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://www.debian.org/">https://www.debian.org/</a></p>\r\n<h2><span id="9-centos">#9 CentOS</span></h2>\r\n<figure><img src="https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/centos-screenshot-1024x576.jpeg" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/centos-screenshot-1024x576.jpeg 1024w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/centos-screenshot-450x253.jpeg 450w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/centos-screenshot-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/centos-screenshot-1536x864.jpeg 1536w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/centos-screenshot.jpeg 1600w" alt="Centos linux distros 2020" width="512" height="280" loading="lazy" />\r\n<figcaption>Centos Screenshot</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>Based on Fedora and Red-Hat, CentOS creates a stable server system that can be used by organizations that want a strong server distribution without the high costs involved.</p>\r\n<p>CentOS is built by the community, just like Fedora and offers highly tested packages for download. Similar to Debian, it&rsquo;s very unlikely for someone to break this OS just because they downloaded something from the package manager.</p>\r\n<p>CentOS is the right fit if you want to build a server but don&rsquo;t want to use the apt package manager.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://www.centos.org/">https://www.centos.org/</a></p>\r\n<h2><span id="10-kali-linux">#10 Kali Linux</span></h2>\r\n<figure><img src="https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/kali-linux-screenshot-1024x623.png" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/kali-linux-screenshot-1024x623.png 1024w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/kali-linux-screenshot-450x274.png 450w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/kali-linux-screenshot-768x467.png 768w, https://cdn.journaldev.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/kali-linux-screenshot.png 1334w" alt="Kali linux best linux distro for cybersecurity" width="512" height="310" loading="lazy" />\r\n<figcaption>Kali Linux Screenshot</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>This distribution is not a daily driver. Instead, Kali focuses on working in a live persistent environment with just about every tool that a cybersecurity enthusiast would want.</p>\r\n<p>Based on Debian, this distribution is stable as well as very easy to use.</p>\r\n<p><strong>If you&rsquo;re interested in cybersecurity or penetration testing, this distribution will provide you with a complete environment for that purpose. </strong>You can focus on learning how to use the tools without worrying about installing them or setting them up.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://www.kali.org/" aria-invalid="true">https://www.kali.org/</a></p>\r\n<h2><span id="conclusion">Conclusion</span></h2>\r\n<p>So as we mentioned before, there is no best distribution. We say this because if you know how to install packages using the package manager in a distribution, you can change any distribution and make it look like any other.</p>\r\n<p>But as a beginner, a fully finished environment is an easier start. Based on what you want a Linux OS for, you can choose from one of the above and start your learning from thereon.</p>', 'reda', 'linux', 'post5f95af78b82fa.png', '2020-10-25'),
(62, 20, 'Top 5 Backend Frameworks to learn in 2020', '<p>Frameworks have become a necessary part of every frontend &amp; backend development in this modern age, as the trend of developments are always growing with the passage of time. It&rsquo;s absolutely stupid to reinvent the wheel for such advanced techniques, assuming that you can reinvent all that. That&rsquo;s why using frameworks supported by millions of developers around the world is a very practical method for developing powerful and interactive applications.</p>\r\n<p>Although every backend framework comes with its own set of pros and cons, there are also a few other circumstances you&rsquo;ll want to take into consideration before making a final decision. In this guide, we&rsquo;ll take a deeper look at both tried and newer frameworks to help you decide which is the best backend framework for you.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What makes a backend framework the best?</strong></p>\r\n<div data-index="1">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>Backend frameworks&nbsp;are judged by many factors. In my opinion, a framework should be versatile. Most of the times backend frameworks&nbsp;are ranked by the coding tools, programming languages the support, &amp; interfaces they offer.</p>\r\n<h2>List of Best Backend Frameworks</h2>\r\n<p>From RESTful APIs to complete MVC frameworks, here are some of the most robust backend frameworks in 2020 you should learn.</p>\r\n<h3>.Net Core</h3>\r\n<p>The main reason why I have chosen .<strong>Net Core</strong>&nbsp;as the best backend framework is its <strong>Versatility</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Are you a Web Developer or want to Develop an App for Mobile or Desktop, If you are a Game Developer or want to work on Machine Learning, your <strong>.Net Core</strong> knowledge will help you.</p>\r\n<p>Here are the results of <strong>Slackoverflow</strong> 2018 &amp; 2019 survey comparison.</p>\r\n<figure><img src="https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.29.45-PM.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 759px) 100vw, 759px" srcset="https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.29.45-PM.jpg 759w, https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.29.45-PM-300x158.jpg 300w" alt="stackoverflow survey 2018 2019" width="759" height="401" data-sizes="(max-width: 759px) 100vw, 759px" data-srcset="https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.29.45-PM.jpg 759w, https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.29.45-PM-300x158.jpg 300w" data-src="https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.29.45-PM.jpg" /></figure>\r\n<p>We can see how quickly<strong> .Net</strong> &amp; <strong>.Net Core</strong> has raised fame as compared to the previous year. After <strong>.Net 5</strong> news, there&rsquo;s no doubt that .Net is going to be the best frameworks in future.</p>\r\n<p>Let&rsquo;s see what is the most loved frameworks according to <strong>Stackoverflow</strong> survey results.</p>\r\n<figure><img src="https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.18.41-PM-1024x416.png" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.18.41-PM-1024x416.png 1024w, https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.18.41-PM-300x122.png 300w, https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.18.41-PM-768x312.png 768w, https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.18.41-PM.png 1065w" alt="most loved frameworks" width="1024" height="416" data-sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-srcset="https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.18.41-PM-1024x416.png 1024w, https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.18.41-PM-300x122.png 300w, https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.18.41-PM-768x312.png 768w, https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.18.41-PM.png 1065w" data-src="https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.18.41-PM-1024x416.png" /></figure>\r\n<p>We can see that <strong>.Net Core</strong> has remained the most loved framework of 2019.</p>\r\n<p>There&rsquo;re many Top Programming Languages Surveys available to choose the best programming language but for the best Backend Framework, there&rsquo;s only one survey by <a href="https://codinginfinite.com/top-back-end-frameworks-survey-poll/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="(opens in a new tab)">CodingInfinite</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Here are the results of developers survey.</p>\r\n<div data-index="2">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<figure><img src="https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Screenshot-2019-11-21-at-2.33.58-PM.png" sizes="(max-width: 820px) 100vw, 820px" srcset="https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Screenshot-2019-11-21-at-2.33.58-PM.png 820w, https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Screenshot-2019-11-21-at-2.33.58-PM-300x151.png 300w, https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Screenshot-2019-11-21-at-2.33.58-PM-768x386.png 768w" alt="top backend framework" width="820" height="412" data-sizes="(max-width: 820px) 100vw, 820px" data-srcset="https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Screenshot-2019-11-21-at-2.33.58-PM.png 820w, https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Screenshot-2019-11-21-at-2.33.58-PM-300x151.png 300w, https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Screenshot-2019-11-21-at-2.33.58-PM-768x386.png 768w" data-src="https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Screenshot-2019-11-21-at-2.33.58-PM.png" /></figure>\r\n<p>The above stats are really interesting. It shows, when it came to the developers&rsquo; community to pick the best backend framework, 66% of developers have chosen <strong>.Net Core </strong>as their first choice.</p>\r\n<h3>Express</h3>\r\n<p><a href="https://expressjs.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Express</a>&nbsp;is a fast, minimalist framework of <strong>Node.js</strong>. It provides a light coating of necessary web application features, without obscuring Node.js features. Furthermore, it&rsquo;s easy to build powerful <strong>Web Services</strong> with the help of various <strong>HTTP</strong> utility methods &amp; middleware available.</p>\r\n<p>A few examples of large websites using Express are: IBM, Uber, Accenture.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unopinionated &amp; Minimalistic</li>\r\n<li>Amazing routing API</li>\r\n<li>A large number of plugins</li>\r\n<li>Setup is simple &amp; straightforward</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Express is based on Node.js &amp; <strong>Node.JS</strong> is on the top on the Stackoverflow Survey result.</p>\r\n<figure><img src="https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.29.45-PM.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 759px) 100vw, 759px" srcset="https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.29.45-PM.jpg 759w, https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.29.45-PM-300x158.jpg 300w" alt="stackoverflow survey 2018 2019" width="759" height="401" data-sizes="(max-width: 759px) 100vw, 759px" data-srcset="https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.29.45-PM.jpg 759w, https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.29.45-PM-300x158.jpg 300w" data-src="https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-1.29.45-PM.jpg" /></figure>\r\n<p>Another thing what makes <strong>Node.js</strong> one of the most popular frameworks is JavaScript. JavaScript the most popular &amp; easy to learn programming language.</p>\r\n<h3>Django</h3>\r\n<p><a href="https://www.djangoproject.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Django</a>&nbsp;is a powerful Python framework that is built with the idea of including almost everything, a developer would want out of the box. Therefore there is less need for third-party plugins &amp; everything in <strong>Django</strong> works together. <strong>Django</strong> however, is built for bigger applications. Therefore, if you&rsquo;re preparing on developing small applications, <strong>Django</strong> may not be the most suitable option as it can make a small project bloated with unnecessary features.&nbsp;Big names such as Youtube, Google, &amp; Instagram use this framework.</p>\r\n<p>A few examples of large websites built on <strong>Django</strong> include: Pinterest, Disqus, Mozilla, National Geographic.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\r\n<div data-index="3">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Extremely customizable</li>\r\n<li>Highly scalable</li>\r\n<li>Encourages rapid development, no need to reinvent the wheel,</li>\r\n<li>Extensive documentation &amp; community</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Python</strong> is the most popular language according to&nbsp;<a href="https://pypl.github.io/PYPL.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">PYPL</a> &amp; almost every survey. That&rsquo;s why developers also want to use their Python knowledge for writing Web Services &amp; developing Powerful Web Applications. That&rsquo;s one of the reasons why Django&rsquo;s popularity has increased so quickly.</p>\r\n<figure><img src="https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-4.46.19-PM.png" sizes="(max-width: 704px) 100vw, 704px" srcset="https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-4.46.19-PM.png 704w, https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-4.46.19-PM-300x177.png 300w" alt="pypl survey" width="704" height="416" data-sizes="(max-width: 704px) 100vw, 704px" data-srcset="https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-4.46.19-PM.png 704w, https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-4.46.19-PM-300x177.png 300w" data-src="https://dottutorials.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Screenshot-2019-08-13-at-4.46.19-PM.png" /></figure>\r\n<h3>Laravel</h3>\r\n<p>The Laravel framework is well-known for building robust We Services &amp; Web Applications. It is loaded with web building components and is said to be full of featured backend web development framework.</p>\r\n<p>Laravel is open-source &amp; follows the <strong>MVC</strong> design pattern. It is a PHP framework for the development of extensive backend web apps, which helps seamless connectivity with the back-end. It is well equipped with powerful command-line tools and help functions.</p>\r\n<p>Laravel was initially introduced as an open-source PHP framework in 2011. It has become popular because of the intuitive interface, database migration, blade template engine etc.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Template Engine</li>\r\n<li>Comes with its own CLI</li>\r\n<li>Eloquent ORM</li>\r\n<li>Powerful template system (Blade)</li>\r\n<li>Database Migration System</li>\r\n<li>Good documentation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Ruby on Rails</h3>\r\n<p>RUBY ON RAILS is one of the most popular MVC based web frameworks developed using Ruby programming language &amp; executed on Linux OS. It offers developers a convenient coding environment, with smooth compilation and testing.</p>\r\n<p>It also provides a smooth transition from back end development &amp; testing to the ultimate stages of the development lifecycle. It has built-in security functions and uses a set of add-ons before the launch of the web application.</p>\r\n<p>The following are some of the unique features of the Ruby on Rails framework.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Symbol garbage collector</li>\r\n<li>Keyword arguments</li>\r\n<li>Turbolinks</li>\r\n<li>Module #prepend</li>\r\n<li>Action Mailer</li>\r\n<li>Action cable &amp; Actionpack Assertions</li>\r\n<li>Rails API</li>\r\n<li>Rake command</li>\r\n</ul>', 'reda', 'programming', 'post5f95b4bfef1b7.png', '2020-10-25');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`post_id`, `author_id`, `post_title`, `post_content`, `post_author`, `post_category`, `post_image`, `post_date`) VALUES
(63, 20, '25 Best Websites To Learn Ethical Hacking in 2020', '<p>Today, many youths want to learn ethical hacking. Fields like security research, ethical hacking, etc were supposed to flourish in the near future. However, learning ethical hacking is not an easy task and it can&rsquo;t be mastered overnight. There were users who purchase online courses or join a training program to learn ethical hacking.</p>\r\n<p>In fact, there are plenty of websites available on the internet which can help you learn ethical hacking in a short time. So, in this article, we have decided to share a list of best websites that share tutorials or guides on ethical hacking.</p>\r\n<div data-index="1">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h2><strong>List of 25 Best Websites To Learn Ethical Hacking in 2020</strong></h2>\r\n<p>On these websites, you can discover several useful articles or courses on ethical hacking and security. So, let&rsquo;s explore the list of best websites to learn ethical hacking in 2020.</p>\r\n<div data-index="3">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>1. <a href="http://www.hacking-tutorial.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow external" data-wpel-link="external">Hacking Tutorial</a></strong></h3>\r\n<p><a href="https://techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/hacking-Tutorial.jpg" data-wpel-link="internal"><img src="https://techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/hacking-Tutorial-1024x576.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" srcset="//techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/hacking-Tutorial.jpg 1024w, //techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/hacking-Tutorial-300x169.jpg 300w, //techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/hacking-Tutorial-768x432.jpg 768w, //techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/hacking-Tutorial-696x392.jpg 696w, //techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/hacking-Tutorial-747x420.jpg 747w" alt="Hacking Tutorial" width="640" height="360" data-ll-status="loaded" /></a></p>\r\n<p>Well, Hacking Tutorial is one of the best and top-rated websites on the list which explains vulnerabilities. You will find several articles on vulnerabilities found on software. Not only that, but the site also lets you download tutorials in PDF format for offline viewing.</p>\r\n<div data-index="4">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>2. <a href="http://www.hackinthebox.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow external" data-wpel-link="external">Hack In The Box</a></strong></h3>\r\n<p><a href="https://techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/hack-in-the-box.jpg" data-wpel-link="internal"><img src="https://techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/hack-in-the-box.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 518px) 100vw, 518px" srcset="//techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/hack-in-the-box.jpg 518w, //techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/hack-in-the-box-289x300.jpg 289w, //techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/hack-in-the-box-405x420.jpg 405w" alt="Hack In The Box" width="518" height="537" data-ll-status="loaded" /></a></p>\r\n<p>It is the second Best Website To Learn Ethical Hacking. This site has hanged significantly through the years and it is rebranded as HITB, and the site is completely transformed into what looks like a WordPress-based platform. Also still Today Hack In The Box remains focused on security and ethical hacking from past years.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>3. <a href="http://www.hackthissite.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow external" data-wpel-link="external">Hack This Site</a></strong></h3>\r\n<p><a href="https://techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Hack-this-site.jpg" data-wpel-link="internal"><img src="https://techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Hack-this-site.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 579px) 100vw, 579px" srcset="//techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Hack-this-site.jpg 579w, //techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Hack-this-site-300x229.jpg 300w, //techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Hack-this-site-80x60.jpg 80w, //techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Hack-this-site-550x420.jpg 550w" alt="Hack This Site" width="579" height="442" data-ll-status="loaded" /></a></p>\r\n<p>If you have little knowledge of the ethical hacking field and searching for resources to expand your hacking skills, then you need to visit this site. It&rsquo;s basically a community of ethical hackers where you can find or share details of your findings. If you have any doubts, then you can directly ask the community.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>4. <a href="http://www.evilzone.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow external" data-wpel-link="external">EvilZone Hacking Forums</a></strong></h3>\r\n<p><a href="https://techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Evil-Zone.jpg" data-wpel-link="internal"><img src="https://techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Evil-Zone.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px" srcset="//techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Evil-Zone.jpg 625w, //techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Evil-Zone-300x230.jpg 300w, //techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Evil-Zone-80x60.jpg 80w, //techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Evil-Zone-547x420.jpg 547w" alt="EvilZone Hacking Forums" width="625" height="480" data-ll-status="loaded" /></a></p>\r\n<p>This is one of the largest communities and forums of hacking on the internet and also the best site to learn to hack. Also, this community likely has the skills and knowledge to answer any programming question you could possibly have on it or outside it. All the tutorials are very sharply explained on this website.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>5. <a href="http://hackaday.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow external" data-wpel-link="external">Hack a Day</a></strong></h3>\r\n<p><a href="https://techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Hack-A-Day.jpg" data-wpel-link="internal"><img src="https://techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Hack-A-Day.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" srcset="//techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Hack-A-Day.jpg 640w, //techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Hack-A-Day-300x203.jpg 300w, //techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Hack-A-Day-621x420.jpg 621w" alt="Hack a Day" width="640" height="433" data-ll-status="loaded" /></a></p>\r\n<p>As the name indicates Hack a day is also another best site to learn ethical hacking on the internet. This website definitely offers an amazing library of information for anyone looking for specific categories like cell phones, GPS or digital cameras, and much much more.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>6. <a href="https://www.eccouncil.org/Certification/certified-ethical-hacker" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow external" data-wpel-link="external">EC-Council</a></strong></h3>\r\n<p><a href="https://techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Ec-Council.jpg" data-wpel-link="internal"><img src="https://techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Ec-Council-1024x486.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" srcset="//techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Ec-Council-1024x486.jpg 1024w, //techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Ec-Council-300x142.jpg 300w, //techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Ec-Council-768x365.jpg 768w, //techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Ec-Council-696x331.jpg 696w, //techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Ec-Council-1068x507.jpg 1068w, //techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Ec-Council-884x420.jpg 884w, //techviral.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Ec-Council.jpg 1177w" alt="Ec Council" width="640" height="304" data-ll-status="loaded" /></a></p>\r\n<p>The International Council of E-Commerce Consultants (EC-Council) is a member-based organization that certifies individuals in various e-business and information security skills. International Council of E-Commerce Consultants, also known as the EC-Council, is the world&rsquo;s largest cybersecurity technical certification body.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>7. <a href="http://www.breakthesecurity.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow external" data-wpel-link="external">Break The Security